# Project Documentation

## Project Title
Responsive Banking UI with Deposit and Withdrawal System

---

## Objective

To design and implement a responsive banking interface that supports deposit and withdrawal operations with real-time balance updates and validation.

---

## Functional Requirements

- Display current account balance
- Allow user input for deposit amount
- Allow user input for withdrawal amount
- Prevent invalid or negative transactions
- Provide responsive design across devices
- Display user feedback for invalid inputs

---

## Technical Implementation

### Front-End Structure
- Semantic HTML layout
- CSS Flexbox for structured layout
- Media queries for responsiveness

### JavaScript Logic
- Event listeners for transaction buttons
- DOM manipulation for updating balance
- Input validation checks
- Conditional logic to prevent negative balance withdrawals

---

## System Requirements

### Hardware
- Minimum 4GB RAM
- Standard modern processor
- 1366Ã—768 display or higher

### Software
- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
- VS Code or any code editor

---

## Core Concepts Demonstrated

- CSS Box Model
- Flexbox layout system
- Responsive design with media queries
- JavaScript template literals
- State management in front-end applications

---

# Conceptual Understanding (Interview Preparation)

### 1. Explain the CSS Box Model components
The CSS Box Model consists of:
- Content
- Padding
- Border
- Margin

These layers determine spacing and layout behavior of elements.

---

### 2. How do media queries enable responsiveness?
Media queries apply different CSS rules based on screen size, resolution, or device characteristics, allowing layouts to adapt to various devices.

Example:
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
        flex-direction: column;
    }
}
